To extract a specific character from a string using an index, you can use the indexing feature provided by most programming languages. Here’s how you can do it in a few popular languages:

### Python
In Python, you can access characters in a string using square brackets with the index inside. Remember that indexing starts at 0.

```python
my_string = "your_string_here"
# Get the 13th character (index 12 because indexing starts from 0)
thirteenth_character = my_string[12]
print(thirteenth_character)

# Get the character at position (x-14)
x = 20  # Example value for x
character_at_x_minus_14 = my_string[x-14]
print(character_at_x_minus_14)
```

### JavaScript
In JavaScript, you can also use square brackets to access characters by index.

```javascript
let myString = "your_string_here";
// Get the 13th character (index 12)
let thirteenthCharacter = myString[12];
console.log(thirteenthCharacter);

// Get the character at position (x-14)
let x = 20; // Example value for x
let characterAtXMinus14 = myString[x - 14];
console.log(characterAtXMinus14);
```

### Java
In Java, you can use the `charAt()` method of the `String` class.

```java
String myString = "your_string_here";
// Get the 13th character (index 12)
char thirteenthCharacter = myString.charAt(12);
System.out.println(thirteenthCharacter);

// Get the character at position (x-14)
int x = 20; // Example value for x
char characterAtXMinus14 = myString.charAt(x - 14);
System.out.println(characterAtXMinus14);
```

### C#
In C#, you can use the indexer provided by the `string` class.

```csharp
string myString = "your_string_here";
// Get the 13th character (index 12)
char thirteenthCharacter = myString[12];
Console.WriteLine(thirteenthCharacter);

// Get the character at position (x-14)
int x = 20; // Example value for x
char characterAtXMinus14 = myString[x - 14];
Console.WriteLine(characterAtXMinus14);
```

Make sure that the index you are trying to access is within the bounds of the string to avoid errors. If the index is out of the string's range, you'll encounter an error or exception, so it's good to add checks for that.
